1
1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,388
Historic documents say
that Pęgów has existed
since the 13th century.

2
00:00:04,388 --> 00:00:08,776
But wait —
people lived here
much earlier!

3
00:00:08,776 --> 00:00:13,164
Amazing finds prove it:
a stone axe

4
00:00:13,164 --> 00:00:17,552
and a stone hatchet
were discovered
right here.

5
00:00:17,552 --> 00:00:21,940
Scientists say
they come from
the Stone Age,

6
00:00:21,940 --> 00:00:26,328
from the Neolithic period.

7
00:00:26,328 --> 00:00:30,716
Imagine — this was
the same time

8
00:00:30,716 --> 00:00:35,104
when pyramids were built
in ancient Egypt!

9
00:00:35,104 --> 00:00:39,493
That was
4 to 6 thousand
years ago.

10
00:00:39,493 --> 00:00:43,881
Amazing, right?

11
00:00:43,881 --> 00:00:48,269
But this is not
the most exciting discovery!

12
00:00:48,269 --> 00:00:52,657
In fields near Pęgów,
a real treasure
was found.

13
00:00:52,657 --> 00:00:57,045
It was a pot
filled with
gold coins

14
00:00:57,045 --> 00:01:01,433
from around
the year 1060.

15
00:01:01,433 --> 00:01:05,821
The treasure weighed
half a kilogram

16
00:01:05,821 --> 00:01:10,209
and had
406 coins.

17
00:01:10,209 --> 00:01:14,597
Among them were coins
of Hungarian kings:

18
00:01:14,597 --> 00:01:17,731
Solomon,
Stephen I,
and Béla I.

19
00:01:17,731 --> 00:01:21,493
There was also a coin
of King Cnut,

20
00:01:21,493 --> 00:01:25,254
the ruler of Denmark
and Britain.

21
00:01:25,254 --> 00:01:29,642
There were coins
of German emperors:

22
00:01:29,642 --> 00:01:33,403
Henry II
and Otto III.

23
00:01:33,403 --> 00:01:37,791
The treasure was likely
linked to an old
trade route

24
00:01:37,791 --> 00:01:42,179
that ran north
of Wrocław.

25
00:01:42,179 --> 00:01:46,567
Why did someone bury
a pot full of gold?

26
00:01:46,567 --> 00:01:50,955
We can only guess.

27
00:01:50,955 --> 00:01:54,090
Maybe it was a merchant
afraid of robbers

28
00:01:54,090 --> 00:01:57,224
who hid his wealth
in a safe place.

29
00:01:57,224 --> 00:02:01,612
Did his plan work?

30
00:02:01,612 --> 00:02:06,000
We don't know.
One thing is sure —
he never came back.
